snippet.textDisplay: Anne with an "e" is indeed "great" if you have the ability to overlook the sappy preachiness of the "social justice terrorists" among the writing staff, who have seen fit to abscond with the the original story in order to  pound the drum of the LGBTQ agenda. It only lasts for a few episodes and you will have to send the kids to bed and and Gram Ma to the other room. It is jarring how they just crammed this agenda in so obviously. It was like seeing a gay pride parade smack dab in the middle of a Christmas pageant or seeing Mick Jagger in a Norman Rockwell painting. But that is what Netflix is all about it seems. There is a preponderance of shows on Netflix that is obviously cramming revisionist propaganda down our throats. They highlight the sexual nature of otherwise wholesome relationships that was in the book. I'm surprised they didn't run with the incestuous possibilities of the Cuthberts relationship. After all, as the apparent theme of this story-line states, "Love is love and takes various forms" and sex is just the expression of love so they say. Anne loved her milk cow...lets not go there.
